			<div id="post-6756" class="post-6756 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-survival-preparedness tag-bol tag-homestead tag-land tag-permacultue tag-real-estate">
			<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/episode-924-lessons-learned-on-the-arkansas-homestead" title="Permalink to Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead" rel="bookmark">Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead</a></h2>

			<div class="entry-meta">
				 <span class="meta-prep meta-prep-author">Posted on</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/episode-924-lessons-learned-on-the-arkansas-homestead" title="11:54 am" rel="bookmark"><span class="entry-date">June 18, 2012</span></a> <span class="byline"><span class="meta-sep">by</span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/author/Modern Survival" title="View all posts by Modern Survival">Modern Survival</a></span></span><span class="comments-link"><span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/episode-924-lessons-learned-on-the-arkansas-homestead#comments" title="Comment on Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead">35 Comments</a></span>
			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->

				<div class="entry-content">
				<div id="tweetbutton6756" class="tw_button" style="float:right;margin-left:10px;"><a href="http://twitter.com/share?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fepisode-924-lessons-learned-on-the-arkansas-homestead&amp;text=Episode-924-%20Lessons%20Learned%20on%20the%20Arkansas%20Homestead&amp;related=&amp;lang=en&amp;count=horizontal&amp;counturl=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesurvivalpodcast.com%2Fepisode-924-lessons-learned-on-the-arkansas-homestead" class="twitter-share-button"  style="width:55px;height:22px;background:transparent url('http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-tweet-button/tweetn.png') no-repeat  0 0;text-align:left;text-indent:-9999px;display:block;">Tweet</a></div><div class="podPress_content podPress_content_audio_mp3">
<div class="podpress_playerspace podpress_playerspace_audio_mp3 podpress_mp3player" style="display:block;" ><div id="podPressPlayerSpace_5"><!-- podPress --></div></div>
<div class="podPress_downloadlinks podPress_downloadlinks_audio_mp3"><a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/6-12/epi-00924-lessons-learned-on-the-homestead.mp3" target="new" title="Download: Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead" class="podpress_downloadimglink podpress_downloadimglink_audio_mp3"><img src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/audio_mp3_button.png" class="podPress_imgicon podpress_imgicon_audio_mp3" alt="" /></a> <span class="podpress_mediafile_title podpress_mediafile_title_audio_mp3">Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead</span> <span class="podpress_mediafile_dursize podpress_mediafile_dursize_audio_mp3">[ 1:12:41 ]</span> <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_5" class="podpress_playlink podpress_playlink_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressShowHidePlayer('5', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/6-12/epi-00924-lessons-learned-on-the-homestead.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;"><span id="podPressPlayerSpace_5_PlayLink" class="podPress_playerspace_playlink">Play Now</span></a><input type="hidden" id="podPressPlayerSpace_5_OrigURL" value="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/6-12/epi-00924-lessons-learned-on-the-homestead.mp3" /> | <a href="#podPressPlayerSpace_5" class="podpress_playinpopup podpress_playinpopup_audio_mp3" onclick="javascript:podPressPopupPlayer('5', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/6-12/epi-00924-lessons-learned-on-the-homestead.mp3', 290, 24, 'The Survival Podcast', '6756', 'Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead', 'The Survival Podcast'); return false;">Play in Popup</a> | <a href="http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/6-12/epi-00924-lessons-learned-on-the-homestead.mp3" target="new" class="podpress_downloadlink podpress_downloadlink_audio_mp3">Download</a></div></div>
<script type="text/javascript">podPressShowHidePlayer('5', 'http://www.survivalpodcast.net/audio/2012/6-12/epi-00924-lessons-learned-on-the-homestead.mp3', 290, 24, 'false', 'http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/plugins/podpress/images/vpreview_center.png', 'Episode-924- Lessons Learned on the Arkansas Homestead', 'The Survival Podcast');</script><div id="attachment_6761" style="width: 260px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><img class="size-full wp-image-6761" title="hugul" src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/hugul.jpg" alt="Hugelkultur Was a Success at the Homestead" width="250" height="153" /><p class="wp-caption-text">Hugelkultur Was a Success at the Homestead</p></div>
<p>As many of you know we are now looking to purchase a larger piece of land in Texas.  That will balance well with the apartment we keep in Arlington providing us living quarters both in the city and the country.  The new land in Texas will become our primary residence.</p>
<p>We are not sure about what to do with the Arkansas property right now.  On one hand it is very inexpensive on the other it would generate a lot of cash if we sold it at this point.  Many listeners who have watched me grow TSP from the early days have expressed a desire to hear exactly why we are not going to make Arkansas our permanent home when we put so much work into getting to a point were we could.   The reality is our property has a LOT going for it, it also has a lot missing from what we currently want.</p>
<p>My hope is today&#8217;s show will help others learn from both our successes and failures so they can make better choices about purchasing property, homesteading, raising livestock, etc.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Join Me Today As We Discuss&#8230;</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Leaving family far behind may be harder then you thought</li>
<li>The importance of feeling &#8220;vested&#8221; in the larger community</li>
<li>As your view of the world changes so does your view of &#8220;perfect property&#8221;</li>
<li>5 acres may be enough, it might not be, how does the land lay</li>
<li>Mountain land may not be all it is cracked up to be, or it might be</li>
<li>Why I feel so strongly now about putting a lot of a property into water structure</li>
<li>Why I am now more interested in daily self sufficiency and less in &#8220;buggin out&#8221;</li>
<li>Thoughts on having an ability to &#8220;house&#8221; additional people</li>
<li>Land that provides the opportunity to really teach others</li>
<li>Livestock I want to work with and why it won&#8217;t work in Ark</li>
<li>Deals are now available that just were not before</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Some general principles we have learned
<ul>
<li>Always have an exit strategy</li>
<li>Invest in property to make it at least 1% better then its class</li>
<li>Mobile homes are fine for what they are</li>
<li>Having no real restrictions rocks</li>
<li>See a property for what it can be but count the cost</li>
<li>You really can&#8217;t go to low on an offer, you really can&#8217;t</li>
<li>The community is as important as the property</li>
<li>Useable land is more important then total land area</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Resources for Today’s Show…</span></strong></p>
<ul>
